 VirusWorkshop Version 4.0 final:
 ---------------------------------

 > VirusWorkshop 4.0 is only for Kickstart 2.04 and higher.


 > It is not allowed to put VirusWorkshop on S.H.I. discs !
 > There are two exceptions:
 > Lars Kristensen and Jan Bo Andersen ( SHI Center in Denmark )


   Hiermit verbiete ich, Markus Schmall, Mallander Computersoftware
   VirusWorkshop zu vertreiben !!!!

   Don`t try to crunch VirusWorkshop. It`s already crunched !


   !!!! Based on serious problems with the new reqtools library (2.2b)
   on some systems, I have included my reqtools preferences file and
   the original 2.2b prefrenceseditor for reqtools in the
   package !!! If VW crashes right at the start (at the Continue or
   at DriveChange), then install the included preferencesfile in ENVARC:
   and in ENV: and reset your machine and try it again. Problems seem
   to appear only at reqtools 2.2b with fully booted system. All routines
   work, if you disable the startup and then starts VW. In my opinion,
   this are internal problems in the reqtools library. Another possibility
   is to reinstall 2.2a or 2.1 !!! I have changed some intern routines
   right now, and hope that it`s a workaround for the problems with it.



   NEWS:
   -----


   - Recognition code for Amiga Fanatic Bootblockvirus added.
   - Recognition code for Rootformatter DV Virus added.
   - Screenmode part in the editor and in the preferences optimized:
     Only GUI modes will be displayed now. Thanks Kai Haseloh for the
     hint.
   - It was possible to activate a sectorcheck on a Ram disk. Fixed
     now. Again thanks to Kai Haseloh.
   - Sometimes you could press at the filerequesters "CANCEL", but the
     function continued. Fixed right now. Thanks to Kai Haseloh for
     this hint.
   - FileID Library will now closed again. Sorry, but now FINALLY
     fixed. Thanks Ingo Schmidt !
   - DMS Check Window was too little and had problems with KingCon.
     Hopefully fixed all problems with it. Thanks Kai Haseloh.
   - DMS overwrote without a requester a disc. I have now added a
     little requester for it. Idea by Kai Haseloh. Thanks again !
   - Improved the locale files again.
   - Added swedish translation for VirusWorkshop by Tauno Pinni.
     Special thanks to you !!!
   - Added recognition code for the Polyzygotronifikator Linkvirus.
   - If you selected DriveChange and canceld the requester, no actual
     drive was shown. Fixed right now. In this case it will be set
     to DF0. Thanks Ingo Schmidt.
   - Some clones from old viruses added, which were already recognized.
   - Fixed DiskType recognition problems. This problems were caused
     by the INFODATABLOCK, which was located only at a word aligned
     adress. Special thanks to Juergen Dreyer for this hint !
   - Added new version of ReqTools Library (2.2c=38.1266).
   - Added recognition code for the JizAnsi virus (13.08.1994)
   - Added recognition code for the Look! BBS virus (14.8.1994)
   - Added recognition code for the Sumpf Gag programm (14.08.1994)
   - Optimized recognition code for the NorthStar 1 BB virus, as a
     result the East Star (NorthStar 1 Clone) will be now recognized,too.
   - Added recognition code for the EastStar installer (15.08.1994)
   - Rewrote FileCheck routine again to fix a little "bug" in it. You
     could not check properly RAM: and CD0: and I fixed the problem
     with the help of the megamighty Ingo Schmidt. Many thanks Ingo !
   - Several new recognition routines for system patches included...
   - Added recognition code for the Decompiler Virus (18.08.1994)
   - Optimized again the routines from the filechecker. Special thanks
     to the almighty Ingo Schmidt for all his help and hints. Now the
     filechecker is faster and much more secure (19.08.1994)


   Markus



                           Tristar & Red Sector inc.`94 - Back to the roots





