 VirusWorkshop Version 3.9 final:
 ---------------------------------

 > VirusWorkshop 3.9 is only for Kickstart 2.04 and higher.


 > It is not allowed to put VirusWorkshop on S.H.I. discs !
 > There are two exceptions:
 > Lars Kristensen and Jan Bo Andersen ( SHI Center in Denmark )


   Hiermit verbiete ich, Markus Schmall, Mallander Computersoftware
   VirusWorkshop zu vertreiben !!!!

   Don`t try to crunch VirusWorkshop. It`s already crunched !

   -VirusWorkshop detects itself on disk, if not, be very carefull !
   -The support the for complete Kickstart 3.1 series would not have
    been possible without the support of VILLAGE TRONIC, many thanks.
   -Many thanks to FISCHER HARD & SOFTWARE, SCHIERHOLZSTR.33, HANNOVER
    for their technical help on my AMIGA.


   Caution: I have heard three time that VirusWorkshop crashes, if
   the new ReqTools library is installed and the old preferences
   from reqtools. Simply use the new reqtools preferences editor
   and/or delete envarc:reqtools.prefs.



   NEWS:
   -----


   - Added recognition code for the Laurine 1.0 BB Virus! (05.07.1994)
     (both , female and male variants, will be recognized !)
   - Removed about 600 Reloc32 entries and optimized the whole code.
     (24.06.1994)
   - Optimized the recognitioncode for the G-Zus packer.
   - Optimized recognition code for a hacked AmiExpress version.
   - Added new version of xfdmaster.library (05.07.1994).  !
   - Added support for the A3000 version of Kickstart 40.70 ! (06.07.1994)
   - Added recognition code for the Intel Gag Loadwb. (08.07.1994)
   - Added recognition code for the VCS-I+II Installer.(08.07.1994)
   - Added recognition code for the Degrad Trojan.(08.07.1994)
   - Added recognition code for the Fileghost Installer II. (08.07.1994)
   - Finally made the locale files CatComp compatible. (10.07.1994)
   - Added new version of FileID Library (6.0). (10.07.1994)
   - Fixed resolution bug: VirusWorkshop screen was always opened with
     the coordinates X*X ! (10.07.1994)
   - Added recognition code for the Lamerfry 1.3b virus (12.07.1994).
   - Added support for the official Kickstart 3.1 A4000 & A2000/A500
     releases from Village Tronic and C=. Thanks again for the fast supply,
     Holger ! (15.07.1994)
   - Added recognition code for Doom Virus + Installer (16.07.1994)
   - Added recognition code for the Lamerkiller Virus. (16.07.1994)

   Markus



